&nbsp;
The Committee highlighted the importance of "prosecuting the careful monitoring activity, also on the web, by police and intelligence forces to identify possible risk situations in the national territory". During the meeting a careful analysis of the terrorist attack in Moscow was carried out also for the purpose of updating anti-terrorism prevention measures already arranged.&nbsp;
<h2> From 7 October 47
The intensive anti-terrorism prevention activity has allowed 47 people to expel, from 7 October to today, for safety reasons, of which 9 with the provision of the Minister of the Interior, has emerged from the meeting. In 2024 there were 23 measures, of which 5 were issued by the Minister, Matteo Pinatedosi>. The Committee, in addition to the Secretary Nicola Molteni>, attended the leadership of police forces and information and security agencies.&nbsp;

