AGI - With a voice not strong but not even appannata>, Pope Bergoglio returned today to read a speech in public.> He did so by receiving members of the Nigerian Christian community who lives in Rome. The Pontiff addressed to the present a reflection lasted a few minutes, in the course of which only once appeared to get attached to the words. Bergoglio emphasized, in his reasoning, "three elements: gratitude, wealth in diversity and dialogue". "Thank you for everything you do and continue to do by witnessing the joyful message of the Gospel. Thank you for the many young people of your community who have responded to the call of the Lord for the priesthood and consecrated life," he began, focusing on the concept of "richness in diversity".
&nbsp;
"Diversity of traditions and languages is not a problem, but it is a gift that enriches the fabric of the Church and of society", he highlighted, "Beware of the danger of not being universal, of closing in isolation - I allow the word - tribal. One should not close oneself in one's own culture, which is a gift that must be offered." The last point is the need for dialogue: "Unfortunately many regions world conflicts and suffering and Nigeria period of difficulty. I invite everyone to foster dialogue and listen to each other, without excluding anyone: on a social and religious political level. I encourage you to be proclaimers of God's great mercy by working for reconciliation between your brothers and sisters."

