AGI - Last night half an hour after midnight the firefighters intervened &nbsp; in via Roma in Chioggia for the fire that involved the ground floor of a flanked house on three levels: deceased a couple of 63 and 58 years and the son 27 years old.
&nbsp;
The alarm was given by some young people who saw the flames coming out of the house and &nbsp; they are also prodigated with a scale to try to &nbsp; to save people. The firefighters arrived from Chioggia, Cavarzere and Mestre with 7 fire-fighting vehicles and 18 operators coordinated by the guard officer the service manager turned off the flames, which dealt with a place on the &nbsp; only ground floor, while the smoke fell into the stairwell, saturating the whole house.
&nbsp;
The firefighters entered with the authoritatives found lifeless people on the second floor as confirmed by Suem's health care. &nbsp; The flames on the ground floor were completely turned off and the property after the reclamation was seized by the firefighters. &nbsp;The rescue operations were completed shortly before dawn

