AGI - Monday on the table of the Council of Ministers should arrive a legislative decree that consists of nine articles and that gives implementation to the principles of delegation conferred to the Government for the reform of the judicial order >. Articles relating to the discipline "of access in judiciary; of the professional evaluations of magistrates; the functioning of the Governing Council of the Court of Cassation and of the judicial councils; tables of the judging offices and organizational projects of the Republic's offices; access to the functions of legitimacy; the conferment of the directives and semi-directive functions and the confirmation in the functions themselves".
&nbsp;
In the explanatory report of the decree we read, among other things, that "in welcoming the observations in this sense formulated in the respective opinions from the Justice Commission of the Chamber of Deputies and the Senate of the Republic" is inserted "a new subparagraph" which "prevents that the oral evidence must be designated by qualified experts for the verification of psychoactive suitability to carry out judicial functions".
&nbsp;
"The guidelines and procedures for carrying out the investigations are determined by the Higher Council of the judiciary of agreement with the Minister," he said. "They will get the appointment to ordinary magistrate - we read in a passage of the draft visioned by the AGI - competitors who will be declared suitable also in the light of the results of the tests in word".
<h2> What will be in the file of the magistrate
In addition, the number of competitions increased from three to four, the negative outcome of which prevents participation in subsequent bands. Paragraph 5 covers the personal file of the magistrate and professional reviews. It is "introduced a norm dedicated precisely to the personal file of the magistrate, "even disciplined (as well as the general provisions on public employees) only by the secondary norm dictated by the Higher Council of judiciary". It is expected - read in the draft - "the institution, at the Higher Council of the judiciary, of the personal file of the magistrate, held in computer mode (as it is now necessary) and intended to collect all the information, acts and documents relating to the professional path of the magistrates whose examination is relevant for the purpose of the evaluation of professionalism". &nbsp;
&nbsp;
The new provision provides that they should be included in the evaluation dossier, year by year: "the table, organizational or other measures identifying the tasks and activities, judicial or extrajudicial, carried out by the magistrate and the annual management programmes prepared; the comparative statistical data on the work carried out; the acts and measures drawn up by the magistrate, the minutes of the hearings to which he participated and the measures relating to the outcome of the affairs dealt with in the successive stages of the procedure and judgment".
&nbsp;
"Those documents will be chosen as a champion," he explains, even if he underlines in the draft that "the Committees of Justice of the Chamber and of the Senate in their opinions have highlighted the opportunity that all the acts and measures prepared by each magistrate and not only those chosen as a champion are inserted in the personal dossier".
&nbsp;
In addition, there must be "the measures or acts produced spontaneously by the magistrate, in the number established by the Higher Council of the judiciary; the organizational measures that, in the face of serious and repeated delays, prepare the targeted disposal plans" with the possible exemptions from the assignments and redistributions of the workloads; the inspection reports, limited to the part affecting the individual magistrate; the acts "with which disciplinary action is promoted and the judgments made during the same procedure, as well as &nbsp; the acts with which the action for accounting and rivalry responsibility is introduced and decided, in cases where professional responsibility is promoted".
&nbsp;
Finally, "the reports of the executives of the office of membership, the authorities, the opinions of the judicial councils and the definitive measures of the Council of superior on the professional evaluations, for the change of functions or for the conferment or confirmation of directives and semi-directive functions" and "the further elements that the Higher Council of the judiciary considers should be inserted".
&nbsp;
Paragraph 3 "refers the subjects entitled to access the file: the members of the Higher Council; the executives of the office, also for the activity of insertion of the acts and measures of their own competence; the magistrate; the members of the judicial councils, on the occasion of drafting opinions concerning the magistrate". While "paragraph 4 finally provides for the expulsion from the file of the acts no longer useful, such as those relating to disciplinary action or the action of rivalry once the magistrate has been prosecuted or has intervened rehabilitation". &nbsp;
